### Test API Examples for REST Client Extension
### Click "Send Request" above each request to test

### 1. Simple GET request - Test a public API
GET https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts/1
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2. Get multiple posts
GET https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts?_limit=3
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 3. Test POST request (creates fake data)
POST https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "My New Post",
  "body": "This is the content of my post",
  "userId": 1
}

###

### 4. Test with headers
GET https://api.github.com/users/octocat
Accept: application/vnd.github.v3+json
User-Agent: VS-Code-REST-Client

###

### 5. Example for when you build your own API
# POST http://localhost:3000/api/users
# Content-Type: application/json
# Authorization: Bearer your-token-here
# 
# {
#   "name": "John Doe",
#   "email": "john@example.com"
# }

### Notes:
### - Click "Send Request" above any request to test it
### - Results appear in a new tab
### - Perfect for testing APIs before implementing them in your code
### - Use ### to separate different requests
